Tab railway station is located on railway line number 35 between Kaposvár and Siófok, in Somogy County. The station has five tracks, including two main lines and several additional sidings used for freight and other purposes. The station building is situated on the northeastern side of the tracks.

Regular passenger trains operate from here toward Kaposvár, Siófok, and Dombóvár. The facility is equipped to handle both passenger traffic and limited freight operations.

The station features a standard passenger information system, and a pedestrian crossing provides safe access between the platforms. The infrastructure is maintained by MÁV Zrt., while passenger services are operated by MÁV-START Zrt.